│ `1`. This simplification is valid because `%flag` is a local │
│ `alloca`, and alias analysis confirms that no other          │
│ instruction can modify its value between the store and the   │
│ load.                                                        │
│                                                              │
│ This initial transformation triggers a cascade of            │
│ simplifications:                                             │
│ 1.  The `load` from `%flag` is replaced by the constant `1`. │
│ 2.  The comparison `%cond = icmp eq i8 %flagv, 0` becomes    │
│ `icmp eq i8 1, 0`, which is folded to `false`.               │
│ 3.  The branch `br i1 %cond, label %loop, label %exit`       │
│ becomes an unconditional branch to `%exit`. This effectively │
│ makes the loop execute only once, rendering the backedge     │
│ from `%loop` to itself dead.                                 │
│ 4.  With the backedge gone, the `phi` node `%phi = phi i1 [  │
│ %cmp, %entry ], [ %c, %loop ]` simplifies to its value from  │
│ the only remaining predecessor (`%entry`), which is `%cmp`.  │
│ 5.  The expression `or i1 %cmp, (xor i1 %phi, true)`         │
│ simplifies to `or i1 %cmp, (xor i1 %cmp, true)`, which is    │
│ equivalent to `or %cmp, (not %cmp)`, always resulting in     │
│ `true`.                                                      │
│ 6.  Consequently, `%not2 = xor i1 %or, true` becomes `xor i1 │
