│ things go wrong. The original logic was `%or = or i1 %cmp,   │
│ (xor i1 %phi, true)`. After replacing `%phi` with `%cmp`,    │
│ this becomes `%or = or i1 %cmp, (xor i1 %cmp, true)`. This   │
│ expression is a tautology (`A | !A`), so it should simplify  │
│ to `true`.                                                   │
│     However, the `opt` log shows a convoluted series of      │
│ replacements:                                                │
│     *   `%not1 = xor i1 %phi, true` is processed.            │
│     *   `%or = or i1 %cmp, %not1` is processed.              │
│     *   `%not2 = xor i1 %or, true` and `%not3 = xor i1 %or,  │
